canonical:
  title: 回宣慶表
  author: 金富佾
  language: lzh
  text: 非常勝事不世異恩實千古之未聞擧一方而祗服中謝 皇帝應三靈之符讖襲累世之宗祧仁之所漸者深則義之所制者衆德之所施者博則威之所屈者多故得神兵一揮率土大定東西南北拓地增疆華夏蠻夷望風束手功業光輝於竹素威靈聳動於乾坤今者飭使節以諭宣與諸邦而同慶便蕃上眷渥縟多儀惠厚及遐固論酬而無計心存事大但忠藎以爲期
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 回宣慶表
  author: 金富佾
  language: lzh
  text: 非常勝事。不世異恩。實千古之未聞。擧一方而祗服。中謝。 皇帝應三靈之符讖。襲累世之宗祧。仁之所漸者深則義之所制者衆。德之所施者博則威之所屈者多。故得神兵一揮。率土大定。東西南北。拓地增疆。華夏蠻夷。望風束手。功業光輝於竹素。威靈聳動於乾坤。今者飭使節以諭宣。與諸邦而同慶。便蕃上眷。渥縟多儀。惠厚及遐。固論酬而無計。心存事大。但忠藎以爲期。
korean:
  title: 경사의 선유에 회답하는 글
  author: 김부일
  language: kor
  text: 예사롭지 않는 좋은 일과 세상에 다시 없을 특이한 은혜가 실로 천고(千古)에 듣지 못했던 바이니, 온 나라가 모두 공손히 순복(順服)합니다.황제께서 삼령(三靈)의 부참(符讖)에 응하시어 누대(累代)의 종사(宗社)를 이으사, 인(仁)으로 깊이 적셔주시매 의(義)로 제어하시는 바가 다수요, 덕으로 널리 베푸시매 위엄으로 굴복시키는 바가 많았나이다. 그러므로 신병(神兵)이 한 번 휘두르매 온 천하가 모두 평정되어, 동서남북으로 땅을 개척하여 강토를 늘리었고 중화(中華)ㆍ만이(蠻夷)가 바람을 따라 손을 묶어 귀순하니, 공업(功業)이 역사에 빛나고 위엄이 천지를 용동(聳動)하나이다.이번에 사절(使節)을 특파하시어 선유(宣諭)하시니, 모든 나라와 함께 경사를 같이 하시어 번국(藩國)에 대한 위의 권고(眷顧)가 거듭내리고, 주신 물품이 풍부하여, 두터운 은혜가 먼 곳까지 미치매 진실로 갚을 길이 없사으나, 마음만은 사대(事大)에 두어 다만 충성으로 결심합니다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0420_010_0160&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: Response to the Imperial Envoy's Proclamation of Congratulations
  author: Kim Bu-il
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Such extraordinary blessings and uncommon grace, granted only once in ages past—never before has the realm heard of such gifts. All beneath heaven bow in reverence and submission.

    The Emperor, responsive to the symbols and prophecies of the Three Spirits, inherits the sacred mandate passed down through generations. As benevolence penetrates deeply, so does righteousness spread widely; as virtue extends far, so does authority command obedience across all lands. Thus with a single sweep of the divine army, the ten thousand realms find peace. From east to west, from north to south, territories expand and borders grow. Both the civilized and the distant peoples, seeing the wind of imperial grace, lay down their arms in surrender. Such deeds shine eternally upon the pages of history, and such majesty makes heaven and earth themselves tremble.

    Now an envoy is sent to proclaim these tidings, that all nations might rejoice together in this celebration. The favor shown to tributary states overflows abundantly, with gifts beyond measure and grace extending even to the remotest corners. Though we cannot truly repay such boundless kindness, we hold steadfast in our hearts the principle of serving the great—our only resolve is unwavering loyalty.
  footnotes:
    - This is a state document, formally acknowledging an imperial envoy's announcement of congratulations, likely regarding a significant military or political triumph of the Chinese court.
    - The 'Three Spirits' (三靈) refers to Heaven, Earth, and Humanity, whose alignment was believed to legitimize imperial rule.
    - The phrase 'serving the great' reflects the tributary relationship between Korea and China during this period.
